The paper focuses on graph visualization and cluster analysis, which are both topics within computer graphics (cs.GR) and data structures (cs.DS). The use of metrics to evaluate the quality of graph visualizations also falls under the category of computational complexity and algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the use of graph visualization in machine learning (cs.CV) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC), which are both relevant sub-categories. Finally, the paper's focus on evaluating the effectiveness of different graph drawing algorithms suggests that it may also fall under the sub-category of social and information networks (cs.SI).
